-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, New World Resources Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-11T12:06:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-new-world-resources-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell for a third day, poised for its longest stretch of losses
in a month. The benchmark slid 0.1 percent to 903.30 as of 1:47
p.m. in Prague.  The following are among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   erased a 2.2 percent decline
after the European Banking Authority said the region’s banks
increased capital reserves by $116 billion and Erste exceeded
the regulator’s targets. The Austrian lender traded 0.1 percent
stronger at 379.8 koruna, and jumped 1.4 percent to 14.96 euros
in Vienna, its home market.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, dropped 0.3 percent to 102.5 koruna, its third
day of losses.  Europe ’s benchmark coal futures contracts fell
0.3 percent to $96 a metric ton in the Netherlands, a fourth day
of declines.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
